Even if we have kids involved in a relationship, you still end up divorced because of the stigma that comes along with it. That can be because of the abuse, infidelity or just being unhappy in a relationship.” This unpleasant stigma makes divorce overwhelming for women.

Overall, divorce from domestic violence “is the pure solution for women in situations were there other options would put them in worse or dangerous situations” (Brewer 2013). Divorcing from domestic violence is less nerving and an easy solution from an abusive situation. Submitted IRB 10 – Survey and Research Paper. Submitted to Deborah Jackson; Honors Thesis Advisor.
